# GLC design system (V7 — full modular parity)

This file carries **exhaustive** content from the legacy monolithic `master/MASTER_RULES.md` (V7 architectural truth, e.g. git ref `2784ba8`), merged with **§8 Section composition** (layers + palette minimums). **Copy mapping** remains in **`copy-writing.mdc`**; **route metadata / DOM SEO** in **`seo-strategy.mdc`**.

## Typography lock (non-negotiable)

- **Headings / display:** **Oswald** only (`--font-oswald` / `font-serif`). Section H2, 3-act headline, stat/card numerals follow scales below.
- **Body:** Longform and general UI use **Source Sans 3** (`--font-source-sans` / `font-sans`).
- **Condensed UI:** **Barlow Condensed** via `font-label` for dense chrome (badges on yellow, some CTAs, ~9px index marks). Do not use `font-label` for full-width section eyebrows — use **`.eyebrow`** instead (same typeface, different utility).
- **Section eyebrows / kickers:** Use the **`.eyebrow`** utility in **`app/globals.css`** (**Barlow Condensed**, **13px**, **700**, uppercase, **0.07em** tracking). On **dark** bands pair with **`text-white`** (solid). On **light** bands use **`text-ink`** or **`text-ink-muted`** for secondary. Avoid low-opacity white for primary eyebrow copy.

## §1 — Layout and grid logic (structural pivots and DOM)

Layout is reactive to **copy volume** and uses a **layered Z-order** for interaction clarity and atmospheric depth.

### Layer stack (Z-order)

| Level | Name | Examples |
|-------|------|----------|
| -1 | Atmosphere | `ClaudeLogicWatermark` (low opacity), ambient motifs (~0.18 opacity, rotated), absolute tonal gradient planes |
| 0 | Base canvas | `section-major` root, `band-light` tonal drift, dark blueprint field with linear gridlines |
| 1 | Substrate | Absolute gradient wash (`inset-0`), image scrims, dark image veils |
| 2 | Structural accents | Top/side rails, **4px yellow** accent borders, 1px section dividers, grid seams |
| 10+ | Interaction plane | `relative z-10` foreground, `bespoke-surface`, `panel-machined`, content shells |

### Two-sentence pivot (volume)

- **≤ 2 sentences:** Standard header stack (`max-w-2xl`, centered or left with `pl-5` spine).
- **> 2 sentences:** Mandatory split-column / asymmetric structure: `grid-cols-12` with text in a **6-column measure** (“measure safety”).

### Compositional strategies

- **Container:** `mx-auto max-w-[min(100%,var(--max))]` (1440px / 1200px cap). Gutters: **28px → 40px → 80px**.
- **Header cluster:** `max-w-2xl` + `pl-5` yellow spine.
- **Raised panel:** `bespoke-surface` + `panel-machined` + asymmetric offset at `lg` (`lg:ml-[var(--dna-stagger-sm)]`).
- **Responsive splits:** Mobile `flex-col` → `md:flex-row` **50/50** for featured sections.
- **Stateful rails:** Horizontal strips with stateful widths (Active **400px** / Inactive **60px**).

## §2 — Tonal rhythm and contrast (chromatic transition)

Sections follow the **Chromatic Transition Rule** — they must not read as isolated slabs.

- **Alternation:** Alternate **`band-dark-field`** and **`band-light`** / light drift. **Two consecutive sections of the same tone = “Visual Flatline”** (avoid unless a deliberate exception is documented).
- **Dark/light thresholds:** **Dark** bands carry high-authority / technical clusters (`text-white/90`, `backdrop-blur-md` glass). **Light** bands carry editorial / longform (`--text-600` sparingly; `text-ink` for labels/body per §6). Each band must meet contrast intent before the next shift.
- **Dark sections (`--ink` field):** Hero, authority, technical data; require readable glass panels where copy sits on imagery.
- **Light sections (`--white`):** Editorial, narrative, case studies; sharp contrast with `--text-600` where appropriate; **high-fidelity raster anchors** where imagery leads.
- **Seam:** At tonal transitions use a **1px section divider** or **4px yellow rail** to mark the break.

## §4 — Mandatory asset logic (always visual)

- **Default:** Every **major section** MUST include a visual asset — **raster**, **vector motif**, or **video scrim** — unless explicitly flagged (e.g. `disableAssets: true` in component contract).
- **Presence:** A section with **no** image/motif/scrim is **“Incomplete DNA.”**
- **Treatment:**
  - **Primary:** High-fidelity raster, `object-cover`; optional `mix-blend-overlay` when background-integrated.
  - **Secondary:** `ClaudeLogicWatermark` ~**0.18** opacity as texture in atmosphere (-1) layer.
  - **Tertiary:** **40×40px** inline SVG icons, `currentColor`, for micro-interactions.
- **Anchor rule:** If copy **exceeds 2 sentences**, the asset must act as a **compositional anchor** (side-car image, split layout, or floating `panel-machined` asset) — not decoration-only background.

