## §6 — Typography architecture (readability-first)

Shift away from muted overlines toward explicit sizing, tracking, and `text-ink` contrast.

### Display and headings (Oswald)

- 3-Act headline: `clamp(58px, 8vw, 118px)`; weights 200/600/700; tracking `-0.02em`.
- Stat number: `clamp(52px, 5vw, 80px)`; weight 700; tracking `-0.04em`.
- Card number: 64px; weight 700; tracking `-0.04em`.
- Section H2: `text-3xl → sm:text-4xl` (`clamp(36px, 3.5vw, 52px)`); weight 600; uppercase; tight leading/tracking.
- Card title / panel H3: 20px (`text-xl → sm:text-2xl`); weight 700; tracking `0.02em`; uppercase.

### Section eyebrows and overlines

- **Eyebrows (preferred):** `eyebrow text-ink` (light band) or `eyebrow text-white` (dark band); secondary: `eyebrow text-ink-muted`. Accent lines: `eyebrow text-[color:var(--y)]`.
- **Legacy class names:** `.label-overline` (light) and `.label-overline-on-dark` match the same **13px Barlow Condensed** eyebrow metrics; use with hero choreography (`hero-eyebrow`) where needed. Do not add `opacity-*` on dark hero eyebrows.
- **Condensed / micro (`font-label`):** 9px side labels; yellow-chip labels with black ink; some CTA rows. Not for full-width section eyebrows.

### Metadata (tabs, stats, CTAs)

- **Tab labels:** `eyebrow` + tab state classes (selected inversion); maintain **44px** min height.
- **CTA primary:** 12–13px; weight 700/800; tracking `0.08em`–`0.14em`; uppercase; often `font-label` or utility text where condensed is intentional.
- **Stat label:** `eyebrow text-ink` on light bands.

### Longform and UI copy

- Intro/body: `text-[15px] leading-[1.72] text-ink sm:text-base` (**15px floor** on light).
- Card description: same as body.

## §7 — Interactive DNA and physics

- **Reveal staging** (viewport threshold **0.5**): BG **0s** → eyebrow **0.4s** → headline **0.5–0.8s** → caption **1.15s** → CTA **1.9s**.
- **Section entrance:** `view-reveal-up` (0.65s, `cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1)`, translateY 16→0). Image **~0.2s** parallax lag vs text when paired.
- **`pivot-expand-reveal`:** 0.85s; 50% slide; **1.02×** X-axis scale tension.
- **Accordion:** 700ms width expansion; 220ms motif drift; `--ease-expo`.
- **Tabs:** `role="tablist"`; selected inversion; `[hidden]` on panels (see §9 for ARIA).
- **Count-up:** 1800ms cubic-out at 0.5 viewport threshold.
- **`.cta-primary`:** 0.2s envelope; hover `translateY(-2px)`; arrow `translateX(4px)`; brightness +10%.

## §8 — Visual hierarchy, palette, and section composition

### Section composition (non-negotiable)

Applies to **every major section** (`section-major`, hero bands, split CTAs).

**1. Minimum contrasting layers (≥3)**  
Stack **≥3 visually distinct planes** (maps to §1 Z-order). Typical choices:

| Plane | Role | Examples |
|-------|------|----------|
| Base | Canvas | `band-light`, `band-dark`, `band-dark-field` |
| Substrate | Image or fill | `next/image`, tonal wash |
| Treatment | Scrim / glass | Gradients, `backdrop-blur-md`, `bg-[rgb(10,12,11,0.45)]` |
| Structure | Rails / seams | 4px `var(--y)`, `border-white/10`, `var(--g200)` |
| Interaction | Foreground | CTA row, `bespoke-surface`, `z-10` shell |

**2. Tri-tonal typography (required)**  
Three distinct **type** color roles per area:

- **Primary:** headings/stats — dark: `text-white` or `text-[color:var(--y)]`; light: `text-ink`.
- **Secondary:** body/ledes — dark: `text-white/90`; light: `text-ink` or `--text-600` sparingly.
- **Tertiary:** metadata / secondary labels — dark: **`eyebrow text-white`** for primary eyebrows; reserve **`text-white/55`** (or lower) for non-eyebrow texture only; light: `text-ink-muted` / `text-400`.

**3. Rule of three (legacy V7)**  
Every section must use **≥3 distinct typographic color tokens**: **Anchor** (yellow or deep charcoal for values/titles), **Narrative** (mid body contrast), **Texture** (low contrast for non-eyebrow metadata — e.g. muted slate on light; avoid using washed eyebrows as the only “white tier” on dark).

**4. Minimum palette presence in UI (≥3 roles)**  
Beyond photo pixels, design must show **≥3** intentional GLC roles — e.g. **`--y`**, **`--ink` / dark glass**, **white tier** (`text-white`, `text-white/90`, `border-white/10`, or `#fff` panel). On light bands: `text-ink` + `--text-600` or muted label + **`--y`** accent.

### Hero metrics cluster (authority row)

Apply **three colors** strictly:

1. **Primary accent:** Yellow core on the **numeric** (e.g. `15+`).
2. **Secondary:** `text-white/90` on **stat labels** (context).
3. **Tertiary:** **`eyebrow text-white`** on **coverage label** and chip text (legible, solid white). Optional softer tints only for non-eyebrow helper lines.

### Rhythm directive (dark vs light)

- **Dark (“authority”):** Yellow → `text-white/90` body → **`eyebrow text-white`** for eyebrows / coverage; optional lower-opacity tokens only for non-eyebrow texture.
- **Light (“editorial”):** Charcoal deep → `--text-600` → muted slate (longform readability).

### Core tokens

- `--yellow-core` / `--y`: `#f2b705`
- `--charcoal-deep` / `--ink`: `#1e1c1a`
- `--white`: `#ffffff`
- `--text-600`: `#6b6560` (sparingly; not default for labels/body)

### Depth and surfaces

- `.bespoke-surface` + `.panel-machined`: machined inset shadow, backdrop depth, micro-grain where defined in CSS.
- Glass: `bg-[rgb(10,12,11,0.45)]`, `backdrop-blur-md`, `border-white/10`.
- Borders: **4px** yellow rails; **1px** seams `var(--g200)`; **1px** section dividers.
- Shape: sharp industrial baseline (`--radius: 0` unless token exception).

## §9 — Accessibility and asset constraints

- **Alt text:** Mandatory for all **primary** images; meaningful, not stuffed with keywords.
- **ARIA for tabs:** `role="tablist"` / `tab` / `tabpanel`; `aria-selected`, `aria-controls`, `aria-labelledby`; roving tabindex where applicable.
- **Tap targets:** **44px minimum** height/width for interactive controls (tabs, links in dense UI).
- **SVG:** Inline icons `currentColor`, **40×40** target footprint where interactive.
- **Raster:** `object-cover` with explicit `width`/`height` or `fill` + `sizes` as appropriate.
- **Line clamp:** Tab titles `line-clamp-2` on small viewports when needed.
- **Measure:** Longform body **≤ ~75 characters per line** (use `max-w-*` / column width — aligns with **`seo-strategy.mdc`** readability).
- **Decorative only:** Motifs and watermarks **`aria-hidden="true"`**.
- **`prefers-reduced-motion`:** Disable count-ups, marquee motion, and parallax transforms for users who request reduced motion.

## V7 audit summary (design-facing)

- **Refactor trigger:** Paragraph **> 2 sentences** → structural layout change (see **`copy-writing.mdc`**).
- **Assets default:** **Assets = true**; see §4.
- **Tonal alternation:** Enforce dark/light rhythm; **no Visual Flatline**; seams per §2.
- **Typography:** Readability-first `text-ink` on light bands; deprecate weak muted overlines for primary labels.

## Portable blueprint (hero metrics block — reference pattern)

Legacy master included a full **TSX** appendix. **Archived source:** [`docs/v7-blueprint/GLHeroMetricsCoverageBlock.reference.tsx`](docs/v7-blueprint/GLHeroMetricsCoverageBlock.reference.tsx) (not imported by the app — pattern reference only). See also [`docs/v7-blueprint/README.md`](docs/v7-blueprint/README.md).

When building stats + coverage clusters on dark glass:

- Shell: `border-white/10`, `bg-[rgb(10,12,11,0.45)]`, `backdrop-blur-md`, `shadow-2xl`, padding `p-6 sm:p-8`.
- **Yellow rule** divider above stats (`bg-[#f2b705]/80` or `var(--y)`).
- Stats: **yellow** value, **`text-white/90`** labels.
- Coverage label: **`eyebrow text-white`** (see **`GLHeroMetricsCoverageBlock.reference.tsx`**).
- Optional chips: `border-white/20`, subtle `bg-white/5`, hover state.

Implementations may follow **`ServicePageTemplate`** hero metrics or a dedicated block component — match §8 hero metrics tri-color logic.

